<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,253,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,289,315]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[321,615,289,315]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
photographed the gall of this species and named it ‘Kashi-me-fukure-zuifushi’ (C-055). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[324,505,325,351]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="539 - 549" refId="ref45007" refString="Ide, T., Wachi, N. &amp; Abe, Y. (2012) Three new species and a new record of Cycloneuroterus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini) inducing galls on Cyclobalanopsis in Japan. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 105 (4), 539 - 549. https: // doi. org / 10.1603 / AN 11172" type="journal article" year="2012">
Ide 
<emphasis box="[367,416,325,351]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
said that the gall corresponds to a new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ide, Wachi &amp; Abe" authorityYear="2012" box="[1042,1161,325,351]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cycloneuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hisashii">
<emphasis box="[1042,1161,325,351]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">C. hisashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,253,423]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,361,387]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Biology.</emphasis>
